%description
In randomized-controlled trials, interim analyses are often planned for
possible early trial termination to claim superiority or futility of a new
therapy. Blinded data also have information about the potential treatment
difference between the groups. We developed a blinded data monitoring tool
that enables investigators to predict whether they observe such an
unblinded interim analysis results that supports early termination of the
trial. Investigators may skip some of the planned interim analyses if an
early termination is unlikely. This tool will provide reference
information about N: Sample size at interim analysis, and T: Total number
of responders at interim analysis for decision on performing an interim
analysis.

